<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="Q" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Quarrel2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Quarrel,</orth> vb. to wrangle, to seek occasion of a fray, to pick a quarrel (German: <emph>Händel suchen</emph>): <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.4.94" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 4, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 3, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 39</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 26</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 26</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tim 3.5.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 5, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.1.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 1, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.222" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 222</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 3, 66</bibl>. With <cit><quote>at:</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.303" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 303</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.182" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 182</bibl>. With <cit><quote>with:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 50</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 18</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 18</bibl> <emph>to q. with</emph> == to be in contrast with, to be contrary to: <cit><quote>some defect in her did q. with the noblest grace she owed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 1, 45</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>yet more --ing with occasion,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.5.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 5, 61</bibl></cit> (contrary to, and seeking to elude, the matter in question; cavilling). <cit><quote>our people q. with obedience,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 1, 9</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>